Usage:                                                                  
  #!./env2 [flags] <interpreter> [<interpreter_args>]                     
  #!./env2 [flags] -f <interpreter> [<interpreter_args>] ~~ <script_args> 
Where [flags] are one or more of:                                       
  -c     : comments mode                                                
  -d     : debug mode                                                   
  -e     : emit (dump) mode                                             
  -f     : find script opts separated by delimiter ~~                   
  -n     : no rc file                                                   
  -p     : preserve empty args                                          
  -s     : strip backslashes                                            
  -x     : expand standard backslash-escaped characters                 
  -h     : this help                                                    
Notes:                                                                  
  * flags can be combined in one string                                 
  * all flags are off by default                                        
Examples:                                                               
  #!./env2 -s -n perl -w                                                  
  #!./env2 bash -x -v                                                     
  #!./env2 -def=@@ python @@ -sf                                          
